\subsection{Understanding the Results}{

\strong{Z-Statistics}: Based on differences in mean ranks between groups
\itemize{
\item Large absolute Z values indicate big rank differences
\item Positive Z: First group has higher mean rank than second
\item Negative Z: Second group has higher mean rank than first
}

\strong{Adjusted P-values}: Control for multiple comparisons
\itemize{
\item p < 0.05: Groups are significantly different
\item p >= 0.05: No significant difference between these groups
