\subsection{P-Value Adjustment Methods}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Bonferroni} (default): Most conservative, multiplies p by number of comparisons
\item \strong{Holm}: Step-down method, less conservative than Bonferroni
\item \strong{BH}: Controls false discovery rate, good for many comparisons
}
